CHOLERA - ECUADOR (02)
**********************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Cholera - Ecuador 980321085405
Cholera & El Nino, WHO statement - Latin America 980401225118
Date: Sun, 31 May 1998 08:07:52 -0400 (EDT)
From: Abramo Ottolenghi <ottolenghi.1@osu.edu>
Source: newspaper El Comercio online, Sat 30 May 1998
<http://www.agestado.com/links/index.htm>

An average of 10 new cases of cholera are registered every day in the port
city of Guayaquil. Cases are appearing in all sections of the city. An
outbreak is also seen in the city of Manta.
The full text of the report in Spanish can be retrieved from the archives
by sending the following message to majordomo@usa.healthnet.org -
get promed-port vl98.n053
